{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"3\n    \n      No Smooth Page Transitions\n      Current: CSS pageIn animation exists (fade + slide up) but gets overridden by Streamlit's rerun behavior. The JS page-loader script tries to intercept clicks but it's fighting Streamlit's framework. Result: pages just \"snap\" in with a brief white flash.\n      Fix: Streamlit fundamentally re-executes the script on navigation. True cross-fade is impossible, but we can: dim on exit, fade-in on entry, use the gold shimmer bar consistently, and prevent the content \"jump\" that looks jarring.\n      Improve perceived smoothness within Streamlit's constraints","choice":"transitions","id":null,"timestamp":1775126447625}
